Third-party source and artifact lineage
=======================================

Arch Linux ARM
  Source: https://archlinuxarm.org/
  Planned use: signed AArch64 Raspberry Pi root filesystem and package
  repository inputs, each pinned by a future build manifest.
  Licenses: packages retain their individual licenses and copyright notices.

Arch Linux
  Source: https://archlinux.org/
  Planned use: pacman, makepkg, mkinitcpio, systemd and package metadata.
  Licenses: see each upstream project and package.

Linux kernel
  Sources: https://github.com/blue-1ms/rpi-linux and
           https://github.com/raspberrypi/linux
  Tested uConsole source commit at repository initialization:
    db7c53b43da7ac8d65ef52328c51c6fb918302e2
  License: GPL-2.0-only for the Linux kernel, subject to per-file notices.
  Kernel source and history remain in the kernel repository; they are not
  relicensed by this control plane.

Raspberry Pi firmware
  Source: https://github.com/raspberrypi/firmware
  Planned use: CM4 boot firmware, DTBs and the official overlay catalogue.
  Licenses: see the upstream distribution and individual files.

ClockworkPi uConsole resources
  Source: https://github.com/clockworkpi/uConsole
  Planned use: hardware documentation and compatibility evidence.
  License: see the upstream repository and individual files.

AK-Rex Raspberry Pi Linux fork and packages
  Sources: https://github.com/ak-rex/rpi-linux and
           https://github.com/ak-rex/akrex-arm-repo
  Planned use: behavioral and source compatibility evidence for uConsole
  panel, backlight, input, audio and power support.
  No binary is incorporated silently; every adopted source change must retain
  its original license and provenance.

blue-1ms uConsole Ubuntu LTS
  Source: https://github.com/blue-1ms/uconsole-ubuntu-lts
  Planned use: hardware validation, diagnostics and A/B policy reference.
  Debian packages and Ubuntu boot hooks are not Arch Linux packages.

blue-1ms mew-console Arch Linux ARM branch
  Source: https://github.com/blue-1ms/mew-console/tree/codex/archlinux-arm
  Audited branch commit at repository initialization:
    338ab106b1705a7e3979a081091b8e8770267da8
  Planned use: requirements source for an optional generic Sway profile and
  first-boot flow. Personal credentials, network state and fixed home paths
  must not be imported.

